    "body": "## Purpose\n\nThis is the first part of Qwen3 MoE + GGUF support (second part: #30118).\n\n#27772 added GGUF parameter checks between required HF parameters.\nI honor this change to make sure that the right model is loaded but had an accidental regression.  All MoE GGUF models stopped working after this patch because of fundamental GGUF and HF differences: one GGUF parameter can map to multiple HF parameters.\n\nTake Qwen3 MoE (Qwen3-30B-A3B-Thinking-2507) for example.\n\n| Format  | Parameter(s) name                                      | Shape(s)                     |\n| ------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------- |\n| HF      | `model.layers.0.mlp.experts.{0..128}.down_proj.weight` | 128 `(768, 2048)` 2D tensors |\n| GGUF    | `blk.0.ffn_down_exps.weight`                           | `(128, 768, 2048)` 3D tensor |\n\nSuch mappings are not handled in #27772 and caused \"Failed to map GGUF parameters\" error.\n\nIn this PR, the author calls such HF parameters *initialized by other means* as **sideload parameters**.\nIt manages its own allow list for the sideload parameters depending on the model architecture + GGUF file format + GGUF-HF differences.\n\nNote that however, despite that this is a required change to support Qwen3 MoE + GGUF, such GGUF file *will not* work out of the box alone (as shown below).\n\n## Test Plan\n\nDownload a quantized (note: *not* BF16) Qwen3 MoE model GGUF file.\nFor instance, you may use [`Q4_K_S` quantization of `Qwen3-30B-A3B-Thinking-2507` from Unsloth](https://huggingface.co/unsloth/Qwen3-30B-A3B-Thinking-2507-GGUF/blob/main/Qwen3-30B-A3B-Thinking-2507-Q4_K_S.gguf).\n\n```sh\nvllm serve \\\n\tQwen3-30B-A3B-Thinking-2507-Q4_K_S.gguf \\\n\t--tokenizer Qwen/Qwen3-30B-A3B-Thinking-2507 \\\n\t--gpu-memory-utilization 0.6 \\\n\t--reasoning-parser deepseek_r1 \\\n\t--max-model-len 8192 \\\n\t--hf-overrides '{\"norm_topk_prob\": true}'\n```\n\nIf this PR is applied alone and you test a Qwen3 MoE GGUF model, , `--hf-overrides '{\"norm_topk_prob\": true}'` to override a sampling parameter is mandatory.\nThis is because, while HF uses the default value of `false`, this value must be generally `true` (and fixed to `true` on GGUF Qwen3 MoE models and I guess that's why they don't contain explicit `norm_topk_prob` parameter).\n\n## Test Result\n\nThe model works just like the regular Qwen3 MoE HF models.\n\nHowever, the output may be garbled without `--hf-overrides '{\"norm_topk_prob\": true}'`.  See #30118 for details.\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [x] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [x] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [x] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n",
